    "Algorithm II presents the pseudo-code of the Data Sharing Phase of the proposed scheme.Algorithm 2 EMR data sharing AnalysisIn this section, the performance and security evaluations of the proposed scheme are given.",
    "Block sizes, block creation times, memory usages, and number of operations were used as performance evaluation parameters.",
    "The entities included in the architecture of the proposed scheme were compared to those reported in studies in the literature for security evaluations.1: Receive a new message request message from a third party entity request message = {e id, message, messageHash (e id) privateKey } 2: if e id is available in the policy list then 3: Get the public key of the third party entity (by the patient) -→ P K e id = (e id) publicKey 4: else 5: break; 6: end if 7: if Hash(message) == messageHash P Ke id then 8: evaluate the request 9: else 10: break; 11: end if 12: if request is approved (by the patient) then 13: Send approved message from the patient to the third party entity -→ approved message = {p (id publicKey) P Ke id } 14: else 15: break; 16: end if 17: Decrypt the p (id publicKey) P Ke id by using (e id) privateKey by the third-party entity -→ p id publicKey = (p (id publicKey) privateKey) P Ke id 18: Decrypt the encrypted storage list saved in the blockchain -→ storagelist = encrpytedStorageList p id publicKey 19: Get encrypted patient's EMR fragments and symmetric encryption keys (by the third party entity) 20: Decrypt encrypted fragments by using symmetric encryption keys -→ f ragment i = encrpyted f ragment (i)secretKey i 21: Merge the fragments in the defragmentation process 22: for i ← 0, count(fragments) do 23:EM R p id + = mergeF ile(f ragment i) 24: end for 25: Result ← EM R p id (by the third party entity) Performance evaluationIn the study, blocks are created using PoW, PoS, and PoA consensus mechanisms, respectively.",
    "These mechanisms are compared to each other in terms of block sizes, block creation times, memory usages, and number of operations.",
    "The consensus mechanisms are written in Java, and the results are obtained using a computer with an i7-7700 HQ CPU, a 2.80GHz processor, and 16 GB RAM."
